    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In philosophy, a theory that holds that in human knowledge objects are grasped and seen as they really are in their existence outside and independently of the mind. It is opposed to idealism, the theory holding that spiritual and ideal is of central importance in the interpretation of experience.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000042061/Webster's Third New International Dictionary (1961)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>哲學理論，認為在人類的認知中，我們對物體之理解與感知，與物體獨立於我們心靈之外的實際存在是一致的。與唯心論(idealism)相反，其理論主張心靈及理性是經驗詮釋的核心。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In de filosofie een theorie die beweert dat objecten door de menselijke kennis worden begrepen en gezien zoals ze werkelijk bestaan, buiten en onafhankelijk van de geest. Dit is het tegengestelde van idealisme, de theorie die stelt dat het spirituele en ideale centraal staan in de werkelijkheid.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
